## Manage Accounts and view statements [by Mohammad Reza]

### Actor (User)
User with a valid account.

### Pre-conditions
User must be logged into the system.
User must have one/many accounts older than 30 days for statement(s).

### Main Flow
1. The user clicks on the one of their accounts on the website's "Account Details" page.
2. The system loads and displays details relevant about the accoount chosen.
3. The user clicks on statements to view statements.
4. The system shows the user the statements for the account chosen. 
5. The user clicks continue to go back to accounts details page. 
6. The system shows user account details page.

### Alternate Flow
- if the user decides to modify an account:
  - after step 2, the user will click on "modify account" and the system will allow modifications done to the account.

### Post Conditions
The user successfully views statements for their accounts or modifies one of their accounts. the system will update the account details for that account to showcase changes
